	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I described the process in <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=4027&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;start=15" class="postlink">this thread</a>. You'll probably not want to keep your dust shield or cover all the way screwed in just for easy access when you play games. With my process, you'll have a tiny bit of space where you can put the game in, but if you don't want to do any of the sanding down, you can just stick plain boards with no cover in.
<br />
<br />The process involves taking the connector out, and flipping it upside down to use the tension end to read games instead of the loose end. But there are some problems you'll encounter when trying to stick a game in the other end of the connector for which I provide a remedy.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


